<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: LMAO</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-10 09:05:12</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>FOR ALL THE IDIOTS. Haste items and procs DO NOT STACK. if you get an exe axe and Fbss you will NOT hit faster, the higher haste will be counted and the lower (in this case Fbss is higher haste exe is lower)will be nulled. Ive asked a bloody Gm in chat kageoni i believe was her name and she told me. STOP BEING STUPID PEOPLE you will never get something this powerfull as a 25/10 weapon you would solo Yellows easily at lv 40.<BR>
Exe Axe-10% ish<BR>
Fbss-15-20% based on users level<BR>
Rbb-35%<BR>
Cof-40%<BR>
Plane Haste Belts 41-49% based on class (yes all meele classes have their own)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Anon</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-11 18:10:40</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>One of the previous posters was correct.  The RBB is 31% haste, and the CoF is 36%.  This information can be gathered from the internal "level" of the haste spell (call it effect since it's permanent) of the item, which can be seen using 3rd party software.  The level determins the haste percentage.<BR>
<BR>
This has also been tested and verified.  If you hit the rogue or monk message boards you can see a listing of the haste percentages of all known items.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Dinthar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-25 11:26:06</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>enchanter/bard buffs and items with perm haste do stack, but 2 enchanter buffs/bard buffs or 2 perm haste items do not stack, the better one automatically overrides the other. Get an fbss or good haste item then get swift like wind... u will notice a dramatic difference without even counting hits per min.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
