<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kental Cowtipper</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-12-04 09:00:29</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The Slaying of the Mighty Dragon, Lady Vox as told by Kental Cowtipper, 52 Warrior of Fennin Ro 12/03/00<BR>
<BR>
 We were 46 people strong. We had around 15 tanks, 6 enchs, several clerics and various other casters. I was assigned to the main tank group, in fact, i was assigned to lead the main thank group, the most prestigous spot. We were given the order and our group rushed in for the initial foray. Life was quickly lost but the 2 clerics grouped with us were vigilant indeed. When the great white dragon was at 3/4, magicians and necros sent their pets in, great spells of fire reigned from the casters fingers as Vox's life slowly dropped.... at around 1/2 the enchanters started casting the spell of man seive, draining the dragons mana for their own... a shadow knight and a bard in our group soon died but we fought on... when the great white dragon dropped, there were great shouts of joy... somehow, our group had managed to get the kill on the dragon (many screen shots were taken).... Eurylacos, the faithful shadowknight looted the dragon...she dropped a Ruined Bolster Belt, a Dragonbone Bracer, and 2 caster bags.... great rejoycing was made at the RBB, one of Vox's rarer drops.... after all corpses had eventually been rezzed... we began rolling... ALL tanks were ordered to do a random 250.... i had a 1 in 15 chance... we rolled... i rolled a 232! i started to get excited... when i noticed once other person had rolled as high as me... we had tied, a rare occurence indeed... this other person was a 46/paladin, assigned to the "emergency tank group"... infact, his blade never even touched Lady Vox's icy flesh.... Well at this, confusement abounded as people tried to figure out what should be done... a reroll was quickly called for... i was swearing up a storm in guild chat and people were telling me " FUCKING DO IT!", "YOU"RE GONNA FUCKING WIN!" i think my guild leader was even in on the shouting, swearing too.. well, i rolled.. i rolled a 17.... the paladin rolled a 196.... the idea of owning one of the best melee items in the game was practically handed to me, then snatched up by a lowly paladin, barely high enough to go to the planes... that is my story of the slaying of the Lady Vox<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
